Taiwan Stocks Movers: Acer, Powerchip Technology, Unimicron

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-09-09T07:00:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/taiwan-stocks-acer-quanta-powerchip-united-microelectronics.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 62.20 points, or 0.8 percent, to
7,610.57. The gauge dropped 1.9 percent this week, the first
decline in three weeks.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT) gained 5.3 percent to NT$37.10, the
highest close since Aug. 4. The worldâ€™s fourth-largest computer
maker booked a gain of about NT$276 million ($9.5 million) from
selling 12.1 million shares in E-Life Mall Corp., Acer said in a
statement to the Taiwan stock exchange.  Powerchip Technology Corp. (5346)  (5346 TT) dropped 1.1 percent to
NT$1.75, a record low. The chipmaker has cut production and
shipments of dynamic random access memory, or DRAM, by 50
percent since August, said Eric Tang, a company spokesman,
confirming an earlier report from the Economic Daily News.  Unimicron Technology Corp. (3037)  (3037 TT) surged 6.9 percent to
NT$42.35. The company said August sales rose 4 percent to NT$4.6
billion from a year earlier, according to a statement to the
